## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="be877-520">`eventid` deve essere maggiore di 0 o inferiore a 65535 o possono verificarsi errori durante l'operazione.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="be877-520">`eventid` should be greater than 0 or less than 65535 or errors can occur in the operation.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="be877-521">Se si verificano errori, è possibile ottenere ulteriori informazioni sull'origine dell'errore controllando il flusso di output del debugger, se si dispone di un debugger al processo di generazione di eventi.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="be877-521">If errors do occur, you can get more information about the source of the error by checking the output stream of the debugger, if you have a debugger attached to the process firing events.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="be877-522">È inoltre possibile cercare gli errori segnalati nel flusso di eventi ETW, se si dispone di un listener ETW per l'origine evento in cui si verifica l'errore.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="be877-522">You can also look for errors reported in the ETW event stream, if you have an ETW listener on the event source where the error occurs.</span></span>  

 <span data-ttu-id="be877-523">Questo metodo protetto consente agli utenti di definire nuovi <xref:System.Diagnostics.Tracing.EventSource.WriteEvent%2A> overload che sono più veloci rispetto a overload specificato.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="be877-523">This protected method  enables users to define new <xref:System.Diagnostics.Tracing.EventSource.WriteEvent%2A> overloads that are faster than the provided overloads.</span></span>   <span data-ttu-id="be877-524">Creazione di un nuovo overload implica codice unsafe.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="be877-524">Creating a new overload involves unsafe code.</span></span>  <span data-ttu-id="be877-525">La procedura di base è stack-allocare una matrice di descrittori dei dati evento che corrisponde al numero di elementi di payload.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="be877-525">The basic procedure is to stack-allocate an array of event data descriptors that matches the number of payload items.</span></span>   <span data-ttu-id="be877-526">Per ogni elemento di payload, impostare le dimensioni corrette e matrice di dati dell'evento di valore. Chiamare <xref:System.Diagnostics.Tracing.EventSource.WriteEventCore%2A> con matrice inizializzata.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="be877-526">For each payload item, set the correct size and value in the event data array.Call <xref:System.Diagnostics.Tracing.EventSource.WriteEventCore%2A> with the initialized array.</span></span>  

 <span data-ttu-id="be877-527">Nell'esempio seguente viene illustrato come aggiungere un <xref:System.Diagnostics.Tracing.EventSource.WriteEvent%2A> overload che accetta quattro argomenti.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="be877-527">The following example shows how to add a <xref:System.Diagnostics.Tracing.EventSource.WriteEvent%2A> overload that accepts four arguments.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="be877-528">Un esempio sarebbe se si dispone di un evento di registrazione che registra una stringa e interi a 3.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="be877-528">An example would be if you have a logging event that logs a string and 3 integers.</span></span>  

```csharp  

[Event(1)]  
public void LogTime(string tag, int hour, int minute, int second)   
{  
    WriteEvent(1, tag, hour, minute, second);  
}  

```  

 <span data-ttu-id="be877-529">È possibile eseguire questa senza chiamare <xref:System.Diagnostics.Tracing.EventSource.WriteEventCore%2A>, ma sarebbe più lento del necessario.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="be877-529">You could do this without calling <xref:System.Diagnostics.Tracing.EventSource.WriteEventCore%2A>, but it would be slower than it needs to be.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="be877-530">Ciò avviene perché Usa matrici e reflection per determinare quali operazioni eseguire.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="be877-530">That is because it uses arrays and reflection to figure out what to do.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="be877-531">Se si accede a questi una frequenza elevata (1000 > / sec), può essere necessario effettuare un rapido helper, come illustrato nell'esempio seguente.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="be877-531">If you log these at a high rate (> 1000 / sec), it can be worth making a fast helper, as shown in the following example.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="be877-532">Il metodo nasconde esistente <xref:System.Diagnostics.Tracing.EventSource.WriteEvent%2A>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="be877-532">The method shadows the existing <xref:System.Diagnostics.Tracing.EventSource.WriteEvent%2A>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="be877-533">In questo modo il codice del chiamante originale (LogTime) non venga modificata, ma il compilatore C# utilizzeranno la versione più specializzata che sarà più veloce.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="be877-533">Thus the original caller code (LogTime) does not actually change, but the C# compiler will use the more specialized version which will be faster.</span></span>  

 <span data-ttu-id="be877-534">Per compilare codice unsafe, è necessario specificare il [/unsafe (opzioni del compilatore c#)](~/docs/csharp/language-reference/compiler-options/unsafe-compiler-option.md) l'opzione del compilatore.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="be877-534">To compile unsafe code, you must specify the [/unsafe (C# Compiler Options)](~/docs/csharp/language-reference/compiler-options/unsafe-compiler-option.md) compiler option.</span></span>  

```csharp  
class AnotherEventSource : EventSource {  

    [NonEvent]  
    public unsafe void WriteEvent(int eventId, string arg1, int arg2, int arg3, int arg4)  
    {  

        fixed (char* arg1Ptr = arg1)  
        {  
            EventData* dataDesc = stackalloc EventData[4];  

            dataDesc[0].DataPointer = (IntPtr)arg1Ptr;  
            dataDesc[0].Size = (arg1.Length + 1) * 2; // Size in bytes, including a null terminator.   
            dataDesc[1].DataPointer = (IntPtr)(&arg2);  
            dataDesc[1].Size = 4;  
            dataDesc[2].DataPointer = (IntPtr)(&arg3);  
            dataDesc[2].Size = 4;  
            dataDesc[3].DataPointer = (IntPtr)(&arg4);  
            dataDesc[3].Size = 4;  

            WriteEventCore(eventId, 4, dataDesc);  
        }  
    }  
}  

```
